00:33.742 --> 00:37.495
{\an8}<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:37.579 --> 00:38.538
{\an8}Who needs real pineapples

00:38.621 --> 00:40.665
{\an8}when you have
one of these babies?

00:40.749 --> 00:42.333
{\an8}<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:42.417 --> 00:43.626
{\an9}- Donnie!
Donnie! Donnie!

00:43.710 --> 00:44.627
{\an8}I really think we should--
- Ah, fuzzy nerd dice!

00:44.711 --> 00:46.838
{\an3}- Donnie!

00:46.921 --> 00:49.924
[both grunting with impacts]

00:50.008 --> 00:52.927
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:53.720 --> 00:56.473
{\an3}- Mikey, next time,
I would appreciate a heads-up.

00:56.556 --> 00:58.475
{\an1}- Okay.
Heads up!

00:58.558 --> 00:59.601
{\an1}Is that...

00:59.684 --> 01:01.811
- [gasps] It is!

01:01.895 --> 01:05.482
{\an8}<i>The Jupiter Jim Moon Buggy!</i>

01:05.565 --> 01:07.609
{\an8}<i>Featured in not one,</i>
<i>not two,</i>

01:07.692 --> 01:08.818
<i>but 60 sequels</i>

01:08.902 --> 01:11.654
<i>of "Jupiter Jim's</i>
<i>Last Trip to the Moon."</i>

01:11.738 --> 01:13.156
<i>Ah!</i>

01:16.367 --> 01:17.786
{\an3}- How could anybody let
that historical gem

01:17.869 --> 01:19.829
slip through their fingers?

01:19.913 --> 01:21.581
- I do not know, Michael,

01:21.664 --> 01:22.749
but we've got to have it.

01:22.832 --> 01:25.752
<i>[stealthy music]</i>

01:25.835 --> 01:27.712
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:27.796 --> 01:29.672
{\an1}- But how are we gonna
get the car?

01:29.756 --> 01:32.550
{\an1}We can't go and talk
to one of those human people.

01:32.634 --> 01:34.677
[loud crash]

01:34.761 --> 01:37.096
<i>[rock music]</i>

01:37.180 --> 01:38.848
- Who the heck are youse?

01:38.932 --> 01:40.058
- Oh, no, a mutant!

01:40.141 --> 01:41.851
{\an3}Wait, we're mutants too.
It's okay.

01:41.935 --> 01:44.729
- Dude, you better hide.

01:44.813 --> 01:46.898
{\an1}There's a human guy
around here.

01:46.981 --> 01:49.859
- Easy, easy.

01:49.943 --> 01:51.778
This is Repo Mantis Salvage.

01:51.861 --> 01:52.695
The guy is me.

01:52.779 --> 01:54.989
- This is your lot?

01:55.073 --> 01:56.574
{\an1}You have to sell us
that moon buggy!

01:56.658 --> 01:58.743
{\an1}Please!
Ah!

01:58.827 --> 02:00.078
{\an1}- Whoa, whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa.

02:00.161 --> 02:01.704
Cool your scramjets, buddy.

02:01.788 --> 02:03.706
This is a negotiation.

02:03.790 --> 02:05.708
We gotta play it smooth.

02:05.792 --> 02:08.752
<i>[bold percussive music]</i>

02:08.836 --> 02:14.926
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:15.009 --> 02:17.720
- So, uh, how much
you gonna pay us

02:17.804 --> 02:20.390
to take this pile of parts
off your hands, amigo?

02:20.473 --> 02:21.558
- Scram.

02:21.641 --> 02:23.184
I got a lot of fenders
to count.

02:23.268 --> 02:26.521
- I see you drive
a hard bargain, sir.

02:26.604 --> 02:28.439
Well, perhaps
I can interest you

02:28.523 --> 02:29.941
in a little coin.

02:30.024 --> 02:32.068
I've got big silver,
small silver,

02:32.151 --> 02:33.987
and I can make it <i> rain</i>
copper, daddy.

02:34.070 --> 02:36.739
<i>[underwhelming musical tones]</i>

02:36.823 --> 02:39.033
<i>[dramatic musical tone]</i>

02:39.117 --> 02:41.327
{\an1}- Hey, you ain't got
nearly enough, but say,

02:41.411 --> 02:44.914
{\an1}I could use a couple
of tough muties like you.

02:44.998 --> 02:48.001
Ever do any repo work?

02:48.084 --> 02:48.918
- Of course!

02:49.002 --> 02:51.796
No.
What's repo work?

02:51.880 --> 02:53.298
- It's when you take stuff back

02:53.381 --> 02:55.925
from deadbeats
who didn't pay for it.

02:56.009 --> 02:57.385
Do a job for me today,

02:57.468 --> 03:00.096
and I'll let you have
that moon buggy thing.

03:00.179 --> 03:02.140
- We're in.
- And...sidebar.

03:02.223 --> 03:04.225
{\an3}Look, Mikey, repo men
have to be mean,

03:04.309 --> 03:06.227
and I don't know
if you know this,

03:06.311 --> 03:07.353
but you're kind of a softie.

03:07.437 --> 03:09.606
{\an1}- That really hurts
my feelings!

03:09.689 --> 03:10.732
{\an1}Oh.

03:10.815 --> 03:11.733
You have a point.

03:11.816 --> 03:13.067
But I can do this.

03:13.151 --> 03:14.611
{\an1}Hard as nails.
Grr.

03:14.694 --> 03:16.404
{\an3}We're in.

03:16.487 --> 03:17.947
What's the skinny, chico?

03:18.031 --> 03:19.949
- I need you to get an RV

03:20.033 --> 03:21.784
from a real shady mutant.

03:21.868 --> 03:23.244
<i>Holes up in the woods</i>

03:23.328 --> 03:24.495
<i>on the wrong side</i>
<i>of the tracks,</i>

03:24.579 --> 03:29.542
<i>in the darkest outskirts</i>
<i>of the bad part of town.</i>

03:29.626 --> 03:32.045
- Thanks for the ride!
Ah!

03:32.128 --> 03:33.129
- I ran a profile on this guy.

03:33.212 --> 03:36.007
{\an3}Lawless loner,
doesn't pay his bills,

03:36.090 --> 03:38.301
{\an3}lives in this
very spooky forest.

03:38.384 --> 03:40.720
{\an3}He is a 98% match
for the Spine-Breaking Bandit!

03:40.803 --> 03:44.265
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

03:44.349 --> 03:45.308
{\an1}- Pfft.
I'm not scared

03:45.391 --> 03:46.643
of some no-good forest dweller!

03:46.726 --> 03:48.895
Let's see him!

03:48.978 --> 03:51.022
There's his RV!

03:51.105 --> 03:53.816
[growling noises]

03:53.900 --> 03:55.318
both: Ah!

03:55.401 --> 03:56.986
{\an1}- That's the biggest
forest dweller

03:57.070 --> 03:58.154
I've ever seen!
- He is totally

03:58.237 --> 03:59.530
gonna break our spines.

03:59.614 --> 04:01.074
{\an3}Maybe we should call
Raph and Leo.

04:01.157 --> 04:03.451
{\an1}- No, no, no, no, no!
We got this.

04:03.534 --> 04:04.994
{\an1}Think of all the boss
adventures

04:05.078 --> 04:06.663
we could have in
the moon buggy!

04:06.746 --> 04:08.247
- Ah, all right.

04:08.331 --> 04:09.666
{\an3}If you are dead-set
on doing this,

04:09.749 --> 04:10.667
we gotta go stealth.

04:10.750 --> 04:13.169
Sneak-jitsu 101:

04:13.252 --> 04:15.713
{\an3}Never let a spine-breaker
get behind you.

04:15.797 --> 04:18.341
[both scream]
- No! He's behind us!

04:18.423 --> 04:19.676
He is directly behind us!

04:19.759 --> 04:22.178
Ah!

04:22.262 --> 04:22.595
Ah!
- Oof!

04:22.679 --> 04:24.681
Ah.

04:24.764 --> 04:27.976
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

04:28.059 --> 04:29.310
- Hey, I'm Todd!

04:29.394 --> 04:31.145
Welcome to Cuddle Cakes
Puppy Rescue,

04:31.229 --> 04:32.689
the puppy-est place on earth!

04:32.772 --> 04:35.066
[laughs]

04:35.149 --> 04:36.609
- Puppies.

04:36.693 --> 04:38.194
Right.

04:38.277 --> 04:40.321
And which one are you having
for dinner?

04:40.405 --> 04:43.449
- Oh, right!
It's dinner time!

04:45.159 --> 04:48.371
<i>[jaunty music]</i>

04:51.040 --> 04:52.333
Hey, you guys want some of my

04:52.417 --> 04:53.751
Internet-famous
homemade lemonade?

04:53.835 --> 04:58.006
I donate it to folks in Alaska
who need a little sunshine.

04:58.089 --> 05:01.884
<i>[gentle music]</i>

05:01.968 --> 05:03.094
{\an1}- Oh, wow.
This is pretty good.

05:03.177 --> 05:05.847
- That honestly tastes
exactly like sunshine.

05:05.930 --> 05:07.223
{\an3}Wow.
And sidebar.

05:07.306 --> 05:11.644
{\an3}Cute puppies,
nonprofit lemonade?

05:11.728 --> 05:13.229
{\an3}This is no
spine-breaking bandit.

05:13.312 --> 05:15.273
{\an1}- He's the nicest guy
in the world.

05:15.356 --> 05:17.191
- But we need that RV.

05:17.275 --> 05:18.735
We gotta be tough with him.

05:18.818 --> 05:20.737
Hard as nails!

05:20.820 --> 05:22.572
[extended slurping]

05:22.655 --> 05:24.699
{\an1}- Got it.

05:24.782 --> 05:26.617
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

05:26.701 --> 05:28.411
{\an3}So, Todd,

05:28.494 --> 05:31.122
{\an1}let's get down to business
about your RV.

05:31.205 --> 05:33.166
- Sure thing!

05:33.249 --> 05:34.500
Could you hold Willis?

05:34.584 --> 05:37.045
{\an3}- Oh, I d--I don't know
if I'm--no!

05:37.128 --> 05:40.631
Aww, you little mischief-maker!

05:40.715 --> 05:41.966
{\an3}Wait a minute.
We're supposed to be talking

05:42.050 --> 05:43.760
about your RV.

05:43.843 --> 05:44.761
- Look, Todd.

05:44.844 --> 05:47.305
{\an1}You haven't made a payment
in two years,

05:47.388 --> 05:48.765
and that means--
- Yeah.

05:48.848 --> 05:51.225
Turns out, all you get
for rescuing puppies

05:51.309 --> 05:51.934
are million-dollar smiles.

05:52.018 --> 05:54.103
[puppy barks]

05:54.187 --> 05:55.772
Ooh, Miho wants
her belly rubbed.

05:55.855 --> 05:58.816
{\an1}- My hard-as-nails brother
and I are here to--

05:58.900 --> 06:01.986
- And I'll call you
Indiana Bones,

06:02.070 --> 06:03.863
and you Little Bones.

06:03.946 --> 06:05.490
- Mikey, come on!

06:05.573 --> 06:06.449
{\an1}Oh!

06:06.532 --> 06:08.493
{\an3}- [laughs] Melvin wants
to play!

06:08.576 --> 06:09.869
Could you toss his ball?
- Okay, fine.

06:09.952 --> 06:13.623
I will toss the ball if you
give us the keys to your--

06:13.706 --> 06:16.542
I am in something squishy.
I am in something squishy!

06:16.626 --> 06:19.003
- Oh, yeah, I am so swamped,

06:19.087 --> 06:20.630
{\an1}I never get
to clean the yard up.

06:20.713 --> 06:23.841
But you guys
are so good at this!

06:23.925 --> 06:25.968
Do you want to grab
a couple shovels?

06:26.761 --> 06:28.888
[Mikey and Donnie grunting]

06:28.971 --> 06:31.349
{\an3}- [sighs]

06:31.432 --> 06:33.184
Why did we just do that?

06:33.267 --> 06:34.811
- I don't know, Michael.

06:34.894 --> 06:36.270
I don't know.

06:36.354 --> 06:38.314
Niceness is his superpower!

06:38.397 --> 06:41.359
- Ah, you guys
must be exhausted.

06:41.442 --> 06:43.027
Why don't you sleep over?

06:43.111 --> 06:44.320
In the morning,
I can hold Sir Chomps-A-Lot

06:44.403 --> 06:47.156
while you guys floss
his giant fangs!

06:47.240 --> 06:49.450
{\an3}- That sounds gr--
no, no.

06:49.534 --> 06:50.326
{\an3}We didn't come here
to help you.

06:50.409 --> 06:52.954
We came here
to repo your RV.

06:53.037 --> 06:54.497
{\an3}- Okay.

06:54.580 --> 06:55.832
Yeah, I guess me and the pups

06:55.915 --> 06:58.167
will just sleep under the stars
tonight.

06:58.251 --> 07:00.002
[distant thunder]

07:00.086 --> 07:01.003
[sniffing]

07:01.087 --> 07:04.048
<i>[morose music]</i>

07:04.132 --> 07:05.758
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:05.842 --> 07:07.260
And every night,

07:07.343 --> 07:11.180
through puppy hurricane season!

07:11.264 --> 07:13.391
[cries]

07:13.474 --> 07:16.269
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:16.352 --> 07:19.272
- I can't do it!

07:19.355 --> 07:21.274
- Okay, Todd.

07:21.357 --> 07:22.775
[clears throat]

07:22.859 --> 07:26.404
How about you trade us
that dusty RV,

07:26.487 --> 07:30.449
and we make you
a new place to sleep, huh?

07:30.533 --> 07:33.411
- [gasps] Really?

07:33.494 --> 07:35.329
And a place to feed
the puppies,

07:35.413 --> 07:38.541
and bathe and diaper
and play with them?

07:38.624 --> 07:40.918
- Yes.
- I don't suppose that--

07:41.002 --> 07:43.754
{\an1}- Yes, obviously, there will be
robot assistants!

07:44.172 --> 07:45.173
- And go!

07:45.256 --> 07:48.968
<i>[upbeat rock music]</i>

07:49.051 --> 07:55.474
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:20.458 --> 08:23.836
Thanks, guys!
I'll never forget you!

08:23.920 --> 08:25.254
And come back

08:25.338 --> 08:26.422
if you ever want
to milk the puppies!

08:26.505 --> 08:30.968
They have eight nipples!
- No, stop! No.

08:31.052 --> 08:32.260
both: Hard as nails!

08:32.345 --> 08:35.097
- All right!
- We did it!

08:35.181 --> 08:37.433
{\an1}Hey, Repo!

08:37.515 --> 08:38.351
One RV, as promised.

08:38.433 --> 08:41.145
Wax up that moon buggy, baby.

08:41.229 --> 08:43.563
- Not bad, not bad.

08:43.648 --> 08:45.107
But what had happened was...

08:45.191 --> 08:46.943
I ain't giving it to you.

08:47.026 --> 08:47.652
Turns out,

08:47.735 --> 08:48.653
dorky Jupiter Jim fans'll

08:48.736 --> 08:50.446
{\an1}pay big bucks just to sit
in that thing!

08:50.529 --> 08:53.407
- What?
We had a deal, buddy-o.

08:53.491 --> 08:55.952
{\an3}- Scrapping is
a tricky business, kids,

08:56.035 --> 08:57.078
and you got tricked.

08:57.161 --> 08:58.955
- We are not leaving

08:59.038 --> 08:59.789
without our moon buggy.

08:59.872 --> 09:02.291
- Hey, the purple one's funny!

09:02.375 --> 09:03.626
- I keep telling you guys
I'm funny.

09:03.709 --> 09:06.003
- I'm gonna break your legs

09:06.087 --> 09:08.673
halfway through...twice.

09:08.756 --> 09:09.423
Ah!

09:09.507 --> 09:10.424
{\an3}- Ha!

09:10.508 --> 09:10.967
Mikey, the magnet!

09:11.050 --> 09:13.094
- Hmm?

09:13.177 --> 09:16.097
<i>[rock music]</i>

09:16.180 --> 09:18.891
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:18.975 --> 09:20.726
- [sputtering]
- A deal's a deal, chico!

09:20.810 --> 09:22.979
{\an3}- Is there anything
magnets can't do?

09:23.062 --> 09:25.940
{\an1}- Ah!
Ooh!

09:26.023 --> 09:29.277
[giddy laughter]

09:29.360 --> 09:30.569
{\an1}Tallyho!

09:30.653 --> 09:32.071
- Eat crater dust, bug man!

09:32.154 --> 09:35.157
- [panting]

09:35.241 --> 09:38.828
[grunts]

09:38.911 --> 09:40.204
[chuckles]

09:40.288 --> 09:42.415
[horn sounds]

09:42.498 --> 09:44.500
{\an3}- Man, this thing
is super slow.

09:44.583 --> 09:45.876
- Of course it is.

09:45.960 --> 09:48.963
It was built for the gravity
of the Moon.

09:49.046 --> 09:51.257
- Give me back
my dork-mobile!

09:51.340 --> 09:54.719
- Moon-core lasers, activate!

09:54.802 --> 09:55.344
Oh...
- Uh...

09:55.428 --> 09:57.430
- Crater dust cloud...

09:57.513 --> 09:58.764
- Should that do anything?

09:58.848 --> 10:00.016
- Zero-atmosphere
Gatling missiles?

10:00.099 --> 10:01.058
{\an3}Ah, nuts.

10:01.142 --> 10:02.143
[both yell]

10:02.226 --> 10:05.104
- [laughs maniacally]

10:05.187 --> 10:06.856
<i>[rock music]</i>

10:06.939 --> 10:08.190
- This is a movie vehicle, pal.

10:08.274 --> 10:11.235
They wouldn't load it up
with advanced lunar artillery.

10:11.319 --> 10:12.528
{\an1}- Not unless
it's the moon buggy

10:12.611 --> 10:15.197
from "Jupiter Jim's
Third Last Trip to the moon,"

10:15.281 --> 10:16.699
which had a fake dashboard

10:16.782 --> 10:18.492
to fool the Plutonians!

10:18.576 --> 10:19.869
Pasta fazool!

10:19.952 --> 10:23.372
I'm kicking in Jupiter Jim
Titan Turbo Mode!

10:23.456 --> 10:25.416
[both cheering]

10:25.499 --> 10:28.461
{\an3}- [growls]

10:28.544 --> 10:33.007
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:33.090 --> 10:34.050
- I can't shake him.

10:34.133 --> 10:36.218
- I'll try
the Gravity Grease 3000.

10:36.302 --> 10:37.428
Crowd: Oil! Ah, oil!

10:37.511 --> 10:40.598
Oil?
This is gonna...

10:40.681 --> 10:42.350
- I think we got
a bunch of people

10:42.433 --> 10:44.018
pretty oily.
Ow!

10:44.101 --> 10:46.687
[horn honking]

10:46.771 --> 10:48.481
- Maybe the bug-zapper button.
- Really?

10:48.564 --> 10:51.567
{\an3}There is a bug-zapper but--
why didn't you try that first?

10:51.650 --> 10:54.695
- It didn't have
a 3000 after it.

10:54.779 --> 10:55.237
- There. Happy?

10:55.321 --> 10:57.740
- Why, thank you.

10:57.823 --> 10:59.200
[electronic humming]

10:59.283 --> 11:02.244
{\an3}- Oh...

11:02.328 --> 11:04.830
What a pretty tone of blue.

11:04.914 --> 11:07.249
Ow!

11:07.333 --> 11:09.168
<i>[spacey electronic music]</i>

11:09.251 --> 11:10.086
both: Hard as nails!

11:10.169 --> 11:13.756
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:13.839 --> 11:15.591
- [laughs]
Those guys.

11:17.259 --> 11:19.595
<i>[thumping techno music</i>
<i>playing]</i>

11:19.678 --> 11:21.722
- Yeah, all right.

11:21.806 --> 11:23.015
{\an1}- Get 'em.

11:23.099 --> 11:23.933
- [grunting]

11:24.016 --> 11:25.434
- I don't think
he's got this.

11:25.518 --> 11:27.520
- Hey! Leave him alone.

11:27.603 --> 11:29.438
{\an1}- What? I'm just saying
he doesn't have this.

11:29.522 --> 11:30.648
- You're just trying
to get in my head.

11:30.731 --> 11:34.068
{\an3}- Oh, my peaches and cream,
he just doubled.

11:34.151 --> 11:37.279
- [coughing and wheezing]

11:37.363 --> 11:39.156
- Rag! Now!

11:39.240 --> 11:41.325
{\an3}- Have I ever told you
how big and beautiful you are?

11:41.409 --> 11:43.619
- No, but thank you.

11:43.702 --> 11:45.621
{\an1}- Uh, he is about to set
a new high score.

11:45.704 --> 11:48.249
{\an1}I can't watch,
but I can't not watch!

11:48.332 --> 11:50.000
- [coughing]

11:50.084 --> 11:55.339
{\an8}[labored breathing]

11:55.423 --> 11:57.633
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:57.716 --> 11:59.927
- You know what they say
about big-time moments?

12:00.010 --> 12:00.886
- Yes, I do.

12:00.970 --> 12:02.179
They say that in big-time
moments,

12:02.263 --> 12:03.264
leaders make--

12:03.347 --> 12:05.349
- Brain!

12:05.433 --> 12:08.936
{\an8}<i>- Game over.</i>

12:09.019 --> 12:10.187
{\an8}- Ow, my brain!

12:10.271 --> 12:12.857
{\an9}- No!

12:12.940 --> 12:13.524
{\an9}Why?

12:13.607 --> 12:15.484
{\an8}- [inhales heavily]

12:15.568 --> 12:16.152
{\an8}[sneezes weakly]

12:16.235 --> 12:18.487
{\an8}- Gesundheit.

12:18.571 --> 12:20.114
{\an9}- Omigosh, omigosh, omigosh,
Splinter's a zombie!

12:20.197 --> 12:24.326
{\an1}- Mikey, zombies are interested
in other people's brains.

12:24.410 --> 12:25.578
- Rat Flu.
This is not a drill.

12:25.661 --> 12:28.789
I repeat,
this is not a drill, boys.

12:32.376 --> 12:33.335
- I feel terrible.

12:33.419 --> 12:35.421
Do I look terrible?

12:35.504 --> 12:36.338
Be honest.

12:36.422 --> 12:38.466
<i>[woman screams]</i>

12:38.549 --> 12:41.552
- Whoa!
- Okay.

12:41.635 --> 12:44.597
- You look great,
not horribly sick at all.

12:44.680 --> 12:46.599
He's horribly sick.

12:46.682 --> 12:48.100
- Look, a flu this intense

12:48.184 --> 12:49.977
is going to affect
all areas of his brain--

12:50.060 --> 12:53.647
I'm talking
the full seven stages--

12:53.731 --> 12:55.733
before his body
naturally heals itself.

12:55.816 --> 12:57.276
- You guys know what
the full seven stages mean?

12:57.359 --> 12:59.653
- Mm-hmm.

12:59.737 --> 13:02.865
- Another chance to get
whatever we want!

13:02.948 --> 13:04.325
all: Yeah!

13:04.408 --> 13:05.493
- But poor Dad.

13:05.576 --> 13:08.078
He must feel terrible.

13:08.162 --> 13:11.040
{\an1}But lucky us, he'll say yes
to whatever we ask for!

13:11.123 --> 13:13.334
{\an1}Whoo-hoo!

13:13.417 --> 13:17.213
{\an3}- Only if we make it all
the way to end of the flu,

13:17.296 --> 13:20.424
the elusive
stage seven.

13:20.508 --> 13:22.343
And we never get there.

13:22.426 --> 13:23.385
{\an1}- This year's gonna be
different.

13:23.469 --> 13:25.679
Nobody's getting bit.

13:25.763 --> 13:27.306
Nobody's getting infected.

13:27.389 --> 13:28.724
{\an1}- When we do
make it to the end,

13:28.807 --> 13:31.352
{\an1}which I'm now calling
the Must Say Yes stage,

13:31.435 --> 13:33.395
what are we gonna ask for?

13:33.479 --> 13:35.022
all: Hmm...

13:35.105 --> 13:36.649
{\an1}- Hmm.

13:36.732 --> 13:38.400
{\an1}Well, this year, I was
thinking we could ask for,

13:38.484 --> 13:40.819
uh, um, er--uh...

13:40.903 --> 13:42.655
{\an3}- Aww, he's got nothing.
We're dead.

13:42.738 --> 13:43.280
- Hey, I got something,
all right?

13:43.364 --> 13:44.281
Like a, uh--

13:44.365 --> 13:46.492
- Uranium!

13:46.575 --> 13:49.203
Oh, we should absolutely
ask for uranium.

13:49.286 --> 13:50.579
I mean, if I could finally
get my hands

13:50.663 --> 13:53.666
on a little of that, we would
be virtually unstoppa--

13:53.749 --> 13:54.542
{\an3}- What about a brick oven
for pizza?

13:54.625 --> 13:56.085
- Who's gonna clean that?

13:56.168 --> 13:59.922
What we should ask for
is matching unicorn onesies.

14:00.005 --> 14:02.591
Those are sick! Pun intended.

14:02.675 --> 14:04.134
And I nailed it.

14:04.218 --> 14:05.177
[all grunting]

14:05.261 --> 14:06.512
{\an3}- Enough.
I got this, all right?

14:06.595 --> 14:07.805
I'm gonna ask Splinter

14:07.888 --> 14:10.349
for something
that benefits all of us.

14:10.432 --> 14:11.433
- This is so exciting!

14:11.517 --> 14:14.270
But terrible for Dad.

14:14.353 --> 14:17.398
[gasps]

14:18.315 --> 14:21.860
- Buckle up, boys.
It's about to get weird.

14:25.197 --> 14:26.240
[air whooshing]

14:26.323 --> 14:29.660
- [babbling]

14:29.743 --> 14:30.286
[razor buzzing]

14:30.369 --> 14:33.622
[all shivering]

14:33.706 --> 14:34.373
- I hate stage one.

14:34.456 --> 14:35.624
{\an1}Think warm
thoughts.

14:35.708 --> 14:39.128
{\an1}Pizza ovens.
Bricks from Italy.

14:39.211 --> 14:40.879
Wood chips roasting.

14:40.963 --> 14:42.423
- We're four hours in.

14:42.506 --> 14:44.675
His fever's
gotta break soon.

14:44.758 --> 14:46.885
{\an3}- I told you guys
to plan ahead.

14:46.969 --> 14:48.137
{\an3}Now I'm sitting here
all toasty.

14:48.220 --> 14:50.306
{\an3}[slurps]

14:50.389 --> 14:50.973
{\an3}[spits]

14:51.056 --> 14:53.392
{\an3}What? Wha--
Why?

14:53.475 --> 14:57.980
- Had to air myself out.

15:00.274 --> 15:02.526
[growls]

15:02.610 --> 15:03.569
[screeches]

15:03.652 --> 15:05.946
[all screaming]

15:08.824 --> 15:11.160
[all screaming]

15:11.243 --> 15:12.286
- Don't eat me!

15:12.369 --> 15:13.704
Raph's tastier!

15:13.787 --> 15:14.830
- Suits on! Suits on!

15:14.913 --> 15:16.123
Donnie, get the device ready.

15:16.206 --> 15:17.499
- Uh, it's ready.

15:17.583 --> 15:20.336
You know, my inspiration
for this device was simplicity.

15:20.419 --> 15:23.005
Why dress something up
with lots of bells and whistles

15:23.088 --> 15:23.714
when you can just let it
speak for its--

15:23.797 --> 15:26.467
- No one has time for this!

15:26.550 --> 15:30.429
[deep rumbling]

15:30.512 --> 15:32.389
[grunts]

15:32.473 --> 15:34.683
- Nice!

15:34.767 --> 15:37.186
All right,
let's get him inside.

15:37.269 --> 15:39.938
- [snarling]

15:42.441 --> 15:43.692
- Okay, this should hold him
for a while.

15:43.776 --> 15:46.153
- And you're sure
this isn't cruel?

15:46.236 --> 15:47.446
- He loves pizza

15:47.529 --> 15:49.573
{\an3}and confined spaces
you can barely breathe in.

15:49.657 --> 15:51.575
- Donnie, is it gonna hold up?

15:51.659 --> 15:54.286
- Most definitely!

15:54.370 --> 15:55.746
- [snarling]

15:55.829 --> 15:58.624
- [screaming]

15:58.707 --> 16:02.419
<i>[hard rock music]</i>

16:02.503 --> 16:05.255
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:05.339 --> 16:06.215
- [snarling]

16:06.298 --> 16:08.217
- Aah!

16:08.300 --> 16:10.094
{\an1}- Mikey, follow me,
and be careful.

16:10.177 --> 16:13.639
{\an1}We can't afford to lose anyone
before stage seven.

16:13.722 --> 16:15.015
- I thought we all agreed

16:15.099 --> 16:18.227
it was now called
the Must Say Yes stage.

16:18.310 --> 16:20.813
{\an3}- It would be easier for me
to be careful

16:20.896 --> 16:23.732
{\an3}if I knew you were gonna
ask for a pizza oven.

16:23.816 --> 16:25.234
- I'm still thinking!

16:25.317 --> 16:27.444
{\an8}- Quick question:
is uranium still on the table?

16:27.528 --> 16:28.070
{\an1}- Ugh!

16:30.030 --> 16:33.784
Where's Splinter?
Mikey, you smell him?

16:33.867 --> 16:36.829
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

16:36.912 --> 16:38.372
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:38.455 --> 16:40.416
- [whimpers]

16:40.499 --> 16:44.211
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:44.294 --> 16:45.546
{\an3}[gasps]

16:45.629 --> 16:47.923
- [sighs]
- [gasping]

16:48.006 --> 16:48.340
- He's not under there.

16:48.424 --> 16:50.092
{\an1}- Uh...

16:50.175 --> 16:51.927
- What?
- [shrieks]

16:52.010 --> 16:54.179
- Use your words.

16:54.263 --> 16:56.724
- He's...on...you.

16:56.807 --> 16:59.560
- What? Heats on stew?

16:59.643 --> 17:01.645
- He's on you.

17:01.729 --> 17:02.688
- He's on me?

17:02.771 --> 17:03.772
{\an1}- Yes.

17:03.856 --> 17:06.233
- [snarls]
- [screams]

17:08.234 --> 17:09.778
- [snarling]

17:09.862 --> 17:13.741
Oh, my favorite son.

17:13.824 --> 17:16.076
- Favorite son? Run!

17:19.038 --> 17:22.624
{\an1}- Ugh, these things
do not breathe.

17:22.708 --> 17:23.876
- I know, right?

17:23.959 --> 17:25.711
{\an3}Uh, now, are we sure
we're safe?

17:25.794 --> 17:27.755
- Calm down.
We're fine.

17:27.838 --> 17:28.797
{\an1}Raph and Mikey have it
under contr--oh, no.

17:28.881 --> 17:30.966
- Stage three. Stage three.

17:31.049 --> 17:33.719
- Oh, little baby blue,
come to Papa.

17:33.802 --> 17:37.639
- Suits on! Suits on!

17:37.723 --> 17:38.724
- Why weren't you
in your suits?

17:38.807 --> 17:39.975
- It was Leo.

17:40.058 --> 17:41.810
{\an3}- No one forced you to,
Donnie!

17:41.894 --> 17:43.645
Ugh, what's that smell?

17:43.729 --> 17:46.815
{\an3}- I love you
this much.

17:46.899 --> 17:49.318
{\an3}- No, no, you don't.
I'm your least favorite!

17:49.401 --> 17:50.652
- Uh, Leo's infected.

17:50.736 --> 17:52.154
Quarantine him.

17:53.363 --> 17:56.825
- Hey, you need me to get
to the Must Say Yes stage.

17:56.909 --> 17:57.826
We need to ask
for the onesies--

17:57.910 --> 18:00.412
Whoa, it is really hot.

18:00.496 --> 18:01.288
Is there a fire?

18:01.371 --> 18:02.498
There's a fire here, right?

18:02.581 --> 18:03.499
The floor is made of lava?

18:03.582 --> 18:04.792
[screams]

18:04.875 --> 18:06.752
- Down to three.

18:06.835 --> 18:08.462
{\an1}All right, fellas,
let's be careful

18:08.545 --> 18:09.838
{\an1}so the rest of us can make sure
we get what we want.

18:09.922 --> 18:12.216
Who's got eyes
on the package?

18:12.299 --> 18:13.217
{\an3}- [gasps]

18:13.300 --> 18:14.676
I lost him.

18:14.760 --> 18:16.470
{\an1}Oh!

18:19.681 --> 18:20.641
[both gasp]

18:20.724 --> 18:23.435
- Hot soup!

18:23.519 --> 18:26.313
- [yelps]

18:26.396 --> 18:27.356
all: Ah!

18:27.439 --> 18:28.357
{\an3}- Oh!

18:28.440 --> 18:30.192
Where'd Splinter go?

18:30.275 --> 18:31.860
all: Huh?

18:31.944 --> 18:33.737
- Guys! I think I felt him!

18:33.821 --> 18:34.988
- Hey, that is my butt!

18:35.072 --> 18:38.033
[all grunting]

18:38.116 --> 18:41.286
Ow! Would everyone please
stop hitting me?

18:43.038 --> 18:43.831
- Now I've really got him.

18:43.914 --> 18:46.542
Take that, itchy fuzzball.

18:46.625 --> 18:49.920
- [groaning]

18:50.003 --> 18:51.880
- Oh, not my lab!

18:51.964 --> 18:54.925
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

18:55.008 --> 19:01.181
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:05.811 --> 19:08.480
- Donnie, you hit?

19:08.564 --> 19:09.857
- No, no, I'm fine.

19:09.940 --> 19:11.567
I just cut myself
on that janky old door.

19:11.650 --> 19:12.943
Everything's okay.

19:13.026 --> 19:14.236
Raph, did you decide
what we're gonna ask for?

19:14.319 --> 19:16.029
{\an3}- Yeah, I got it.
I'm gonna ask for--

19:16.113 --> 19:20.075
- [clears throat]
- Huh? What?

19:20.158 --> 19:23.495
- ♪ I'm... ♪

19:26.957 --> 19:29.251
- I can't feel my ears!
Nothing is worth this!

19:29.334 --> 19:32.921
{\an3}- We're so close.
Only two stages left.

19:33.005 --> 19:35.591
- And three
totally healthy turtles left.

19:35.674 --> 19:37.259
Man, why is it so hot in here?

19:41.430 --> 19:43.765
Oh, you're gonna get squat
from Splinter without Donnie,

19:43.849 --> 19:46.852
not without ol' Donnie!

19:46.935 --> 19:48.687
I'm the brains
behind this operation!

19:48.770 --> 19:50.772
[sneezes]

19:50.856 --> 19:53.150
{\an1}- Uh, what stage
are we on now?

19:55.360 --> 19:56.945
- Okay, okay, okay.
Listen, listen, listen.

19:57.029 --> 19:58.822
Okay, we open on noodle shop.

19:58.906 --> 20:01.116
It's raining.

20:01.199 --> 20:05.037
Lou Jitsu--
hot soups, two assassins,

20:05.120 --> 20:08.040
then wham--
interdimensional doorway opens,

20:08.123 --> 20:09.166
and out walks...
♪ Dun-dun-duh ♪

20:09.249 --> 20:13.337
Jupiter Jim,
and we smash to titles!

20:13.420 --> 20:14.963
{\an3}- This is amazing.
Keep going.

20:15.047 --> 20:16.465
- We're almost
at stage seven.

20:16.548 --> 20:19.593
{\an1}This is the closest I've been
to success, uh, ever.

20:19.676 --> 20:23.263
{\an3}- [sneezes]

20:24.139 --> 20:25.223
We're done.

20:25.307 --> 20:26.516
Raph is totally
gonna blow this.

20:26.600 --> 20:31.521
He has no idea what to ask for,
which means--

20:31.605 --> 20:33.023
Getting hot.

20:33.106 --> 20:34.608
It's like I'm on the sun here.

20:34.691 --> 20:37.653
- [chuckles]

20:37.736 --> 20:38.695
I'm not gonna blow this.

20:38.779 --> 20:41.531
- Raphael, I love you,
my brother,

20:41.615 --> 20:43.325
but you do tend to fail
in big moments.

20:43.408 --> 20:47.704
Pishposh.
But that's what makes you you.

20:47.788 --> 20:48.830
Now bring it in, buddy.

20:48.914 --> 20:51.500
I'm gonna hug you
till a smile comes out.

20:51.583 --> 20:53.669
- Enough!

20:53.752 --> 20:55.587
Raph's got this,
'cause in big-time moments,

20:55.671 --> 20:59.716
leaders make big-time shots,
and I'm big-time!

20:59.800 --> 21:00.759
- [hissing] He must say yes.

21:00.842 --> 21:02.844
Make him say yes.

21:02.928 --> 21:03.845
- Enough!

21:03.929 --> 21:04.846
Don't mess this up, Raph.

21:04.930 --> 21:05.847
Don't mess this up.

21:05.931 --> 21:07.724
- Don't forget we only get

21:07.808 --> 21:10.227
to ask for one thing,
my little Raph-a-doodle.

21:10.310 --> 21:13.522
- I know exactly
what I'm asking for.

21:18.568 --> 21:21.697
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

21:21.780 --> 21:24.074
- [moans and sniffles]

21:24.157 --> 21:25.909
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:25.993 --> 21:28.370
- Master Splinter,

21:28.453 --> 21:30.956
I know you'll say yes
to whatever I ask for.

21:31.039 --> 21:32.833
I want you to give--

21:32.916 --> 21:36.586
- Raph-a-doodle a hug!

21:36.670 --> 21:38.880
Everybody loves hugs!

21:38.964 --> 21:40.132
{\an1}- What? No!
Anything but that!

21:40.215 --> 21:43.510
- [laughing]
Come here!

21:43.593 --> 21:44.469
{\an1}- Oh! Ow!

21:44.553 --> 21:45.762
- [smooching]

21:45.846 --> 21:47.097
- [sneezes]

21:47.180 --> 21:48.890
- Ooh, flu.

21:48.974 --> 21:51.893
Papa wants a new bike.

21:51.977 --> 21:52.436
<i>[bicycle bell dings]</i>

21:55.147 --> 21:57.065
<i>[sneezes]</i>

21:57.149 --> 21:58.150
<i>Uh-oh.</i>
